goals.question: What is the correlation between fertility and life expectancy?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of fertility vs life_expect
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if there is any relationship between fertility and life expectancy. If there is a negative correlation, it could indicate that countries with higher fertility rates have lower life expectancies.

goals.question: What is the distribution of fertility across countries?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the spread of fertility rates across different countries. It could help us identify countries with high or low fertility rates.

goals.question: What is the distribution of life expectancy across countries?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the spread of life expectancies across different countries. It could help us identify countries with high or low life expectancies.

goals.question: What is the trend of fertility and life expectancy over the years?

goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if there is any trend in fertility and life expectancy over the years. It could help us identify if there is any improvement in life expectancy with a decrease in fertility rates.

goals.question: What is the relationship between normalized fertility and normalized life expectancy?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of n_fertility vs n_life_expect

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='fertility', y='life_expect', hue='country', legend='brief')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between fertility and life expectancy?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Fertility')
    plt.ylabel('Life Expectancy')
    plt.legend(loc='upper right', bbox_to_anchor=(1.2, 1), title='Country')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='fertility', bins=20, color='blue', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['fertility'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['fertility'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of fertility across countries?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Fertility")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='fertility', data=data, label='Fertility', color='blue')
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='life_expect', data=data, label='Life Expectancy', color='green')
    plt.title('What is the trend of fertility and life expectancy over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Value')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='n_fertility', y='n_life_expect', hue='country', legend='full')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between normalized fertility and normalized life expectancy?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Normalized Fertility')
    plt.ylabel('Normalized Life Expectancy')
    plt.legend(loc='upper right', bbox_to_anchor=(1.3, 1), title='Country')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
